BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Text] Two sound bombs were thrown underneath one of the 
coaches of the blue train at Haydarpasa Station in Istanbul last 
night. No one was killed or injured in the incident. 
  According to information received from Istanbul Security 
Directorate officials, at 2330 last night, unidentified persons 
threw two sound bombs under the blue train scheduled to leave 
Istanbul for Ankara at 2345. The noisy explosion of the bombs 
caused panic among the passengers waiting to board the train. 
Bomb experts who arrived at the scene of the incident found and 
defused a time bomb ready for explosion in one of the coaches. 
The blue train eventually left for Ankara at 0110. 

